<subSubSection pageNumber="601" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="601">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="601">Note: 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Liliopsida" family="Juncaceae" genus="Juncus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomeratus">Juncus glomeratus L.</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="601">Amoen. Acad.</emphasis>
4: 481. 1759) was regarded by Stearn (in Geck &amp; Pressler, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="601">Festschr. Claus Nissen</emphasis>
: 632. 1974) as an orthographic variant of 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Juncaceae" genus="Juncus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conglomeratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="601">J. conglomeratus</emphasis>
L.
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="601">Sp. Pl.</emphasis>
1: 326. 1753). This seems plausible, because the phrase name used by Magnol (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="601">Bot. Monsp.</emphasis>
: 635. 1676) is cited as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Juncaceae" genus="Juncus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conglomeratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="601">J. conglomeratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Linnaeus in 1753. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Liliopsida" family="Juncaceae" genus="Juncus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glomeratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="601">J. glomeratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
never appears again.
</paragraph>
